@NODE "General" "General Information"


                     @{b}      .:General information:.       @{ub}                  
@{fg shine}
                         (___                   ___)
                            /___________________\

@{fg text}
  1st of all, if they are included in your package, look at the screenshots
     (the pictures descripe the door alot better than I can in words! 8)

    Tired of your users always are writing slower than you, and it pisses
                                  you off?

     Ever wanted to be able to write at the same time as your user while
                                  in chat?

     Ever wanted to (like on Cnet) execute commands directly from chat?

        Ever wanted a splitscreen chatter, but found that the few in
                            existence were CRAP?

       Ever felt like a normal chat was just too boring with the same
                        design / style all the time?

@{fg shine}
  @{b}    Well, then you got the right door now, this product is BRILLIANT! @{ub}
@{fg text}

    The biggest door I've EVER written (and i've written quite a few now)
     The source is far over 1500 lines and the compiled door fills over 
           110K !!! the is one massive block of superb doorstuff!

   Check out the screenshots.. and you'll know that this baby is fiine! 8)


    The biggest door I've EVER written (and i've writte quite a few now)
     The sourcer is far over 1500 lines and the compiled door fill over 
            80K !!! the is one massive block of superb doorstuff!

   Check out the screenshots.. and you'll know that this baby is fiine! 8)





@ENDNODE

@NODE "Features" "Features"


                              @{b}  .:Features:.   @{ub}                            
@{fg shine}
                         (___                   ___)
                            /___________________\
@{fg text}
                   GUI directly on your /X or S!X screen!

            SYSOP to USER splitscreen chatter with double-cursors

         You can execute commands (like from the mainmenu) by typing
      in the chatter /command for example :     /s    show your status
       all commands works, incl. up/downloading exept for G (goodbye)
       Both sysop and user can use this feature! After the command are
                 executed the bbs returns to the chatting...

      You can make your OWN designs, and even change to another design
                             while chatting!!!!

        Very flexible configuration of the designs, you can even make
      a side-by-side chat or a "normal" over-and-under chattype.. only
                           YOU set the limits! 8)

   The chatter remembers EACH users longest chat/ total chats / total time
   in chat ect. lots of stuff, and you can create TOP10 chatter bulletins
                   with the util included in the package!

      The chatter can also display REALTIME and CHATTIME (and lots more
    features) WHILE chatting, so you can always see for how long you have
                               been chatting!

                            Online configuration!

                      DEL clears the current chatwindow

   Capture feature! When capture is activated ( using the on-screen GUI )
    is remembers and saves everything written by user and sysop, AND it's
     all being saved in a seperate capture-file for each user. That way
    it's easy and fast to locate a specific chat, if you wan't to recall
                    what you and your user talked about!



        @{b}     Massive code and testing - this baby is fiiine! 8) @{ub}



@ENDNODE

@NODE "Installation" "Installation"


                            @{b}  .:Installation:. @{ub}                            
@{fg shine}
                         (___                   ___)
                            /___________________\
@{fg text}

     There's icons with the package ( in Installstuff/ ) just copy them
          to the right dirs.. you know the drill, you are a sysop!

    I also supplied you with a @{fg shine}CHATSTART.txt@{fg text} for your BBS:NODEx/ so when
   your pager starts a chat or you press F1..  spli7chat is automatically
                                  started!

  You might change your CHATEND.txt to something, like a logo or something
  I use a big logo that sais C'YA L8R (save a bit of time, typing it every
                               time myself 8)

   If you want to RESET the stats (like the topchatters ect.) just delete
    all files in the dir called "DATA/"  that way, the chatter starts as
                      if it was opened the first time!


    The first thing I suggest you do, it start it up - and press the gui
     button: CONFIG   ... then make some hotkeys for you personal use...
                    The two other "checkmark boxes" are:


     @{fg shine}  Autocapture@{fg text} - well of'coz turn capture on at every chat-start!

    @{fg shine}   AutoDesign@{fg text} -  checks if the users have less than 24 lines (like
                     most PC terminal programs have, and uses the internal
                     chatdesign (works even if the user have only 23 lines)
                     The chatter STILL remembers you farvorite design
                     and uses that one, when a user comes with enough lines.



@ENDNODE

@NODE "Designs" "How to make new designs"


                     @{b}    .:How to make new designs:.  @{ub}                     
@{fg shine}
                         (___                   ___)
                            /___________________\

@{fg text}
   Make the design (the background) with any ansi editor, (like PROAnsi or
   HyperANSI), then save it in DESIGNS/ with the number you desire + .txt
                                in the end...

   Now make a new textfile with the configuration for the design, for the
    commands you can use, just look in one of the many supplied examples!
                          and save it as number.cfg

  Start up the chatter and press TAB, the type the number.. c if it works!


   Heres just a bit of tips if you are not really into all the ansi stuff
                                 and codes..


         ESC[y;xH    Will place the cursor at location x,y on your
                     screen... example:   ESC[14;2H

         ESC[3xm     Change pen colour (x = colour 0-7)
                     example ESC[33m

         ESC[4xm     Change background colour, like pen...

         ESC[0m      Changes to normal writing style.. (like a reset
                     of the colour ect)

         ESC[1m      bold writing (4=underline 3=itallic etc.)

         ESC[32;41m  the ; conbines to codes to make the ansi command
                     fill less space...


     NOTE! due to some wierd bug/fault i amiexpress, colour 0 and 7 are
  swapped on the sysop's screen, I deal with this by replacing ALL ESC[37m
   with ESC[0m (white colour) in my ansi screens, mabye this will work for
                   you too, if not - just don't do it ! 8)

  @{b}   Should be enough to get you started! try and learn - the best way! @{b}




@ENDNODE

